line_1: Ye silent, solemn, strong, stupendous heights,
line_2: Whose terror-striking frown the school-boy frights

line_1: No more I climb those toilsome heights,
line_2: For me no more the path invites

line_1: " For, wanting strength, none e'er can reach the heights
line_2: "Where Virtue sits, and Genius wings her flights;
